@DATABASE "Default"
@Ver$ "Multiple Paste V1.65 (01/28(98)"
@author "Heiko Schröder"
@Index MAIN
@remark requires MultiView

@NODE "Main" "Multiple Paste V1.65 for Finalwriter"
@TOC "MAIN"
                               @{fg shine}»Multiple Paste V1.65«@{fg text}

is an ARexx-Script for Finalwriter to copy and paste an unlimited number of objects
(grouped or ungrouped) in a few seconds.
At the same time the copies can be displaced and/or rotated.

BTW: This is the renamed macro "Insert Several".

                           @{" " link "Install"} Installation for FW3, FW4 + 5

                           @{" " link "Benutz"} How to use

                           @{" " link "Sonst"} Author

                           @{" " link "Hist"} History

                           @{" " link "Future"} Future

 Sorry, for my poor english. If you want, you can translate my german guide
 and send it to me. You can find the german guide at the Aminet.

                      biz/swood/FW_MEf.lha

 Thanks.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

   MPaste_V3.fw - for FinalWriter 3
   MPaste.fw    - for FinalWriter 4, 5 und higher


If you already use an other version of »MPaste.fw«:

1. Copy »MPaste.fw« in your FWMacros-Drawer.



If you haven't used »MPaste.fw« before:

1. Copy »MPaste.fw« in your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start the program »RexxMast«.

3. Start »Finalwriter«.

4. Open the menu "User - Other - Preferences...". 

         * "Action" - New
         * "Name of menu" - MPaste
         * "Command" - "Type" - ARexx-Script
         * "Command" - "Select" (MPaste.fw)
         * "HotKey" - F9
         * "Accept"
         * "Save"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutz" "How to use"
@TOC "MAIN"

            Select the object(s) you want to copy.

            Start the macro using the Hotkey (F9).
            Input the number of copies, horizontal and vertical
            displacement and the rotation.
            Now you also can select the page where the objects
            should be pasted.

                                   Thats all.

            You can find examples in @{fg fill}»FW_MPaste-Doc.fw«@{fg text}.
            Load this document in FinalWriter.



@ENDNODE

